# Financial Math Readability

This project is extended by "vibe coders" (non-technical users using AI). Complex financial math must be easily understandable by a layperson.

- **Explain the "Why" and "What"**: Every mathematical calculation must have a plain-English comment explaining exactly what it represents in the real world.
- **Avoid cryptic variable names**: Use descriptive, full-word variable names (`annualInflationRate` instead of `infR`).

```javascript
// ❌ BAD: Unclear math and cryptic variables
const r = b * (1 + i) - w;

// ✅ GOOD: Accessible, well-commented logic
// Calculate the new portfolio balance after one year.
// 1. Grow the current balance by the market return rate
// 2. Subtract the annual withdrawal amount
const nextYearBalance = currentBalance * (1 + marketReturnRate) - annualWithdrawal;
```
